<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Swinge" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Swinge,</orth> to whip: <cit><quote>you --d me for my love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 1, 88</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>now will he be --d for reading my letter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.392" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 392</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I would have --d him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.197" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 197</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I had --d him soundly,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 130</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>s. me them soundly forth unto their husbands,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. V, 2, 104</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>saint George, that --d the dragon,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.288" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 288</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I will have you soundly --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.4.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 4, 21</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.4.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 4, 21</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>